// =============================================================================
// core/eval/mod.vr — Stdlib surface for evaluation strategies
// =============================================================================
// Layer: Standard Library / Evaluation
// =============================================================================
//
// Evaluation-strategy machinery for embedding non-default reduction
// orders into Verum programs:
//
//   * `cbpv.vr` — Call-by-Push-Value (Levy 1999). Polarises the
//     value/computation distinction explicitly: `value` types
//     have first-class duplication and erasure, `computation`
//     types are forced exactly once. Provides a uniform framework
//     for embedding both call-by-value and call-by-name reduction
//     in the same source language; the basis for the
//     core-language IR's evaluation contract and the bridge to
//     `core.action.monads.io` (Io as the canonical `F U value`
//     forced computation).
//
// Future additions (V1.5): cbn.vr (call-by-name), cbnf.vr
// (call-by-need / call-by-strict-need), normalisation-by-
// evaluation primitives (NbE).
// =============================================================================

module core.eval;

public module cbpv;
